      <p style="color: rgb(7, 7, 7);">Doctors and hospitals use a medical history of a patient to review his/her health history. It’s a very important part of their workflow <br> to ensure they’re providing the best care and treatment. A patient’s medical history may include details about <b>past diseases, illnesses running in <br> the family, previous diagnoses, medical abstract, therapies, allergies, and medication. </b> <br> Yes, this is not the whole picture but with the help of a detailed medical history, doctors can see health patterns of patients over time at a glance.</p>
